. 1-2 stellar radii). Red-shifted absorption is much more common around\nHerbig Ae stars than Be stars, suggesting that Herbig Be stars may accrete via\na boundary layer rather than along magnetic field lines.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Jun 2015 20:23:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-09"}
